title: For Sale:  1894 Winchester
postcontent: This is a sweet little carbine, 20" barrel, 6 round magazine, lever action 30-30 Winchester 1894, manufactured between 1982 and 1992. This was the year range in which they stopped making them with half cock safeties and before the last generation with those god awful cross-bolt safeties. Its in excellent shape, with only one or two tiny, faint scratches and a couple tiny dings/dents on the stock. The rifling is sharp and the bore shiny, I suspect it might have been unfired when I bought it, and I've only put 20 rounds through it, myself. The trigger is crisp and light, the action smooth and positive. As the picture shows, it has a sling and swivels installed. The sling is well worn - a leftover from another rifle I used the have - but serviceable. I have a set of Winchester factory scope mounts for it, and a Bushnell Banner 3-9x50 with 1" rise rings, all included with the sale.There is absolutely nothing wrong with this rifle. I got out of rifle shooting for a few years and tore up my shoulders pretty bad, and now I just can't handle the recoil anymore. My loss, your gain!Not interested in trades, unless you have something plus cash on your end that really grabs my eye. Honestly, cash is preferred. Willing to meet within reasonable distance. I work long and early days, but my evenings are pretty free. Looking to sell fast.
